2. The groups of varieties referred to in paragraph 1 shall be composed of the following varieties:
Group I:
Altesse double (Italian quetsche), PrĂŠcoce favourite, Belle de Louvain, Conducta, Early Rivers, Kirk's Blue, Jefferson Gage, Luetzelsachser (early Luetzelsachsen quetsche), Anna Spaeth, Ersinger (early Ersingen quetsche), Zimmers (Zimmer quetsche), Buehler  (early Buehl quetsche), Burbank, Florentina, Goccia d'oro, Reine-Claude, Czar, Victorias, Damsons and Santa Rosa;
Group II:
Altesse simple (common quetsche, Hauszwetschge), Reine-Claude d'Oullins, Sveskeblommer, Ruth Gerstetter and Ontario.
3. The entry prices of imported products are to be compared:
(a) with the prices fixed for group I where the imported products belong to varieties other than those shown in (b);
(b) with the prices fixed for group II where the imported products belong to the following varieties: Altesse simple (common quetsche, Hauszwetschge), Reine-Claude d'Oullins (Oullins Gage), Sveskeblommer, Ruth Gerstetter, Ontario, Wangenheimer (early  Wangenheim quetsche), Pershore (yellow egg) Mirabelle, Bosniche and Ortenauer.
